text: Sulzbach-Rosenberg (West Central Bavarian: Suizboch-Rosnberg or Suizbach- Roasnberg) is a municipality in Amberg-Sulzbach, a district (Landkreis) in the Upper Palatinate. It is situated approximately northwest of Amberg, and east of Nuremberg. The town has two parts: Sulzbach in the west, and Rosenberg in the east. == Districts == Etzmannshof Kauerhof Niederricht Siebeneichen Forsthof Kempfenhof Obersdorf Stephansricht Gallmünz Kleinfalz Prangershof Stifterslohe Großalbershof Kropfersricht Prohof Sulzbach-Rosenberg Großenfalz Kummerthal Rummersricht Untermainshof Grottenhof Lindhof See Unterschwaig Grund Lobenhof Seidersberg == References == Category:Amberg-Sulzbach
